{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"0655fa9bcabd95449e38695ec5d4e010","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"\n\nThese were all answered earlier in this session — here's the concise recap:\n\n**1. Per-fact revalidation instead of all-or-nothing**\nCurrently `verifyFactsheetStatic` throwing marks the whole factsheet stale. Catch per-fact failures and only reject individual facts, preserving facts that still verify. The `rejected_facts` field already exists in the output — just use it granularly.\n\n**2. Distinguish hash-changed from selector-actually-changed**\n`findChangedFiles` flags any file with a mismatched hash. But a changed hash doesn't prove the cited selector text moved. Recheck each `selector` + `snippet_hash` in changed files before marking stale — avoids false stale-marks from unrelated edits.\n\n**3. Schedule LLM re-verification after N days even on clean static pass**\nAn `llm_verified` factsheet can go stale semantically without file hashes changing. Track `refresh_age_days`; if it exceeds a config threshold for an `llm_verified` factsheet, log `llm_reverify_scheduled` and mark `needs_prepare` rather than `active/fresh`. The existing trust-state semantics are unchanged — this pre-empts consults from trusting an aged factsheet."}],"model":"MiniMax-M2.7","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":116309,"output_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0},"service_tier":"standard","context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"b299724c-1497-410c-96dd-2f782477c674","uuid":"efc82822-fc24-4ac6-b0c1-800fc2ebd41e"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","is_error":false,"duration_ms":6864,"duration_api_ms":6838,"num_turns":1,"result":"\n\nThese were all answered earlier in this session — here's the concise recap:\n\n**1. Per-fact revalidation instead of all-or-nothing**\nCurrently `verifyFactsheetStatic` throwing marks the whole factsheet stale. Catch per-fact failures and only reject individual facts, preserving facts that still verify. The `rejected_facts` field already exists in the output — just use it granularly.\n\n**2. Distinguish hash-changed from selector-actually-changed**\n`findChangedFiles` flags any file with a mismatched hash. But a changed hash doesn't prove the cited selector text moved. Recheck each `selector` + `snippet_hash` in changed files before marking stale — avoids false stale-marks from unrelated edits.\n\n**3. Schedule LLM re-verification after N days even on clean static pass**\nAn `llm_verified` factsheet can go stale semantically without file hashes changing. Track `refresh_age_days`; if it exceeds a config threshold for an `llm_verified` factsheet, log `llm_reverify_scheduled` and mark `needs_prepare` rather than `active/fresh`. The existing trust-state semantics are unchanged — this pre-empts consults from trusting an aged factsheet.","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"b299724c-1497-410c-96dd-2f782477c674","total_cost_usd":0.078618,"usage":{"input_tokens":2737,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":115616,"output_tokens":285,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"MiniMax-M2.7":{"inputTokens":2737,"outputTokens":285,"cacheReadInputTokens":115616,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.078618,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[],"terminal_reason":"completed","fast_mode_